==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seared
<hw>Seared</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Scorched; cauterized;
hence, figuratively, insensible; not susceptible to moral
influences.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A <qex>seared</qex> conscience and a remorseless heart.</q>
<rj><qau>Macaulay.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Searedness</ent>⟦br⟧
